@risdenk my responses don't seem to showing up for whatever reason.

Re: headers being stored lowercase on insert: I'm not sure the headers should be changed on insert as they are likely stored in specific ways by the table creators and intended to be displayed that way.

And as for the index issue I've updated that in the latest patch to resolve any issues that could have caused.

@jameschen1519 I don't think the test failures are related to your change. 

> (On that note, is there any good way to check the Surefire reports/view build artifacts?)

The Travis build details are linked in the pr and then you go to the specific build and build log. That has the same output if you were to run locally.
